to the editor one of the more bizarre statements in thursday night 's vice presidential debate was dick cheney 's assertion that the government had mostly nothing to do with his recent financial success front page oct 6 in fact the government had everything to do with it does mr cheney a former defense secretary think he got the chairmanship at halliburton on the basis of his proven corporate management expertise or was it more for the contacts in the united states and in foreign governments that he developed in his years on the federal payroll these connections have paid off handsomely for mr cheney and for his company martin e cobern cheshire conn oct 6 2000

